Largest Element in an Array
For finding the largest element in the array. We take a variable largest and assign the minimum value (INT_MIN).
Then we will traverse the array if current element of  the array is greater than the largest element .
Then we will assign current element to the largest element .We will repeat this process until all the element of the array is completed.
class Solution {
  public:
    int largest(vector<int> &arr) {
        // code here
       int n = arr.size();
       int lar=INT_MIN;
       for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
           if(arr[i]>lar){
           lar=arr[i];
           }
           
       }
       return lar;
    }
};
